# Arenet — Docker build context exclusions.
# Step S.1.
#
# The Docker build context is rooted at the repo. We exclude:
#   - Build artefacts that get regenerated in-image (the frontend
#     build output, Go test cache, local `arenet` binary).
#   - Editor / OS noise (.vscode, .DS_Store).
#   - VCS internals (.git is large + irrelevant for the build).
#   - Doc-only directories that don't ship in the binary.

# Editor / OS noise.
.DS_Store
.vscode
.idea
*.swp

# VCS internals.
.git
.gitignore
.gitattributes

# Skill / plugin metadata (Claude Code, etc.).
.claude

# Frontend build artefacts (regenerated in stage 1).
web/frontend/node_modules
web/frontend/build
web/frontend/.svelte-kit

# Backend build artefacts.
/arenet
/data
/tmp

# Test caches.
**/*_test.go.cache

# Local dev databases.
*.db
*.db.bak

# Documentation — useful in the repo, not in the image.
docs/
README.md

# Existing CI / GitHub config.
.github/
